You don't think it's
too edgy for Pepsi?

12:41.494 --> 12:43.897
No, no, no, no.
This is the song!

12:43.931 --> 12:45.432
This is the song.
Oh, yeah.

12:45.465 --> 12:47.434
We can tone down the
edges if we need to.

12:47.467 --> 12:49.436
I got the studio
booked. Come on.

12:49.469 --> 12:51.939
Let's go. Come on.

12:51.972 --> 12:53.740
Well, I don't know if we should
do it now, because...

12:53.773 --> 12:55.809
Yo, why is your mama's
jacket here?
Oh, that's her jacket?

12:55.843 --> 12:57.577
She always leaving stuff
over here. Come on.

12:57.610 --> 12:59.112
And record this dang song.

13:00.113 --> 13:02.249
Acting like a damn fool.

13:02.282 --> 13:04.651
(elevator bell dings)

13:05.685 --> 13:07.487
Anika?

13:07.520 --> 13:08.788
Oh, my God. (chuckles)

13:08.822 --> 13:10.958
Hi, Rhonda.
Hi.

13:10.991 --> 13:12.492
I was just here
getting my favorite smoothie,

13:12.525 --> 13:13.493
the Soul Cleanser.

13:13.526 --> 13:15.295
Are you okay?

13:17.164 --> 13:18.598
You know what?
I feel like my soul

13:18.631 --> 13:19.933
could use some
cleansing, too.

13:19.967 --> 13:21.768
Want me to come?

13:21.801 --> 13:23.770
Okay.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.273
ANIKA: By the way, you look
amazing. You're barely showing.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.008
Well, for a long time,

13:28.041 --> 13:30.110
we didn't want to have
kids, for many reasons,

13:30.143 --> 13:33.780
but when this
happened...

13:33.813 --> 13:35.148
I don't know.

13:35.182 --> 13:37.150
It's honestly the
happiest I've ever been.

13:37.184 --> 13:38.185
Really?

13:38.218 --> 13:39.652
Yeah.

13:39.686 --> 13:41.488
And then there's
this added bonus,

13:41.521 --> 13:44.524
because, turns out, babies are
like kryptonite for Lucious.

13:44.557 --> 13:46.126
Wait, what?
(chuckles)

13:46.159 --> 13:47.961
Well, do you remember
how he was around Lola?

13:47.995 --> 13:49.963
He just completely
melted around her.

13:49.997 --> 13:51.464
Oh, yeah, he did.

13:51.498 --> 13:52.799
It's just
totally bizarre,

13:52.832 --> 13:56.503
because after being completely
iced by him for years,

13:56.536 --> 13:59.439
this pregnancy has
changed everything.

14:01.174 --> 14:04.077
I mean, he'll drop by
my house just to chat.

14:04.111 --> 14:05.078
Really?

14:05.112 --> 14:06.146
Isn't that crazy?

14:06.179 --> 14:07.847
Wow.

14:15.188 --> 14:16.990
(computer rings)
Hey, Mom?

14:17.024 --> 14:18.325
Ma?

14:18.358 --> 14:20.060
Where are we
with your song, Jamal?

14:20.093 --> 14:21.828
I kind of think
I should do some tweaking

14:21.861 --> 14:23.330
to the song myself, you know?

14:23.363 --> 14:24.697
So you working with Jamal?

14:24.731 --> 14:26.699
That's why I can't
get you to help me

14:26.733 --> 14:28.835
with the biggest battle
of my life?

14:28.868 --> 14:30.270
The battle for Dynasty?

14:30.303 --> 14:32.205
It's not what you think, Hakeem.

14:32.239 --> 14:34.241
How come nothing I do
is good enough for you?

14:34.274 --> 14:35.875
What makes you love Jamal
more than me?

14:35.909 --> 14:38.478
Boy, come over here
and sit down.

14:44.952 --> 14:47.087
Look, I'm sorry
I hurt you, okay?

14:47.120 --> 14:49.923
But this deal
is the biggest thing

14:49.957 --> 14:51.724
to ever happen to Jamal.

14:51.758 --> 14:53.793
And if I can
make it happen,

14:53.826 --> 14:55.895
then maybe I can get Jamal
back here with us.

14:55.929 --> 14:56.896
Well, him?

14:56.930 --> 14:58.731
What about me? Us?

14:58.765 --> 15:01.234
You keep working with Jamal,
I'm gonna tell Lucious.

15:01.268 --> 15:03.937
You know what you sound like?

15:03.971 --> 15:05.405
A snitch bitch.

15:05.438 --> 15:07.740
What?
Yeah.

15:07.774 --> 15:09.209
And what, you gonna
snitch to Lucious?

15:09.242 --> 15:10.978
The man who's trying
to take your name?

15:11.011 --> 15:11.979
Really?
I...

15:12.012 --> 15:13.446
Yeah, I thought
your little punk ass

15:13.480 --> 15:15.782
toughened up, but I
guess I was wrong.

15:15.815 --> 15:18.151
All right, I'll hold this one.

15:18.185 --> 15:21.821
But you better get on point, or
I'm gonna air you and Jamal out.

15:21.854 --> 15:22.822
(chuckles)

15:22.855 --> 15:24.624
Okay, you the boss.

15:24.657 --> 15:26.159
Now get your ass in there

15:26.193 --> 15:28.761
so we can get you
ready for this battle.

15:28.795 --> 15:30.430
I'll meet you
in the studio.

15:30.463 --> 15:31.464
Okay.

15:34.701 --> 15:36.336
(sighs)

15:36.369 --> 15:37.837
LUCIOUS:
Same problem, all the way.

15:37.870 --> 15:39.306
Oh, that's crazy.
(groans)

15:39.339 --> 15:41.308
That was crazy.
I'm tired.

15:41.341 --> 15:44.277
Yeah, so, anyway,
I dug up a mountain of dirt

15:44.311 --> 15:45.945
on your friend Jago Locke.

15:45.979 --> 15:48.781
I mean, it was easy.

15:48.815 --> 15:51.951
He airs it all out.

15:51.985 --> 15:54.621
You can't blackmail a man
who flaunts his foulness.

15:54.654 --> 15:57.957
Look, I know you
want this, Pop.

15:57.991 --> 16:01.494
Every bone in my body says
that we should back out now.

16:01.528 --> 16:04.964
No. Dre's got Beats,
Jay has Tidal.

16:04.998 --> 16:07.000
Empire needs Swiftstream.

16:07.034 --> 16:08.701
If you're worried about Mimi,
Pop, we can...

16:08.735 --> 16:11.304
No, no, that bitch needs to
worry about me! Same with Jago!

16:11.338 --> 16:14.207
Same with you two!
Same with Hakeem!

16:14.241 --> 16:16.976
Same with everyone if we don't
start making some moves soon.

16:17.010 --> 16:19.912
I'm sick and tired of being
out here on this damn ledge.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.516
(sighs)

16:23.550 --> 16:25.652
Okay.

16:25.685 --> 16:27.854
Only way we do this
is to get Mimi

16:27.887 --> 16:29.989
to go in with us
to mitigate the risk.

16:30.023 --> 16:32.025
Damn right.

16:34.094 --> 16:35.528
Yeah.

16:37.864 --> 16:39.866
(knocking)

16:43.903 --> 16:45.905
Hey.

16:47.440 --> 16:49.576
Somebody's in a funk.

16:49.609 --> 16:51.678
(laughs)

16:51.711 --> 16:53.546
You never confirmed for tonight.

16:53.580 --> 16:55.348
Sorry, babe.
I just been hella focused.

16:55.382 --> 16:58.051
Oh.

16:58.085 --> 17:00.520
The thing with Freda.

17:00.553 --> 17:02.555
Yeah. Like, Anika,
can I be honest?

17:02.589 --> 17:04.691
Yeah.
I wish
I hadn't done this.

17:04.724 --> 17:07.026
The way Lucious came at me
got me feeling like...

17:07.060 --> 17:09.062
like I'm floating
in outer space or something.

17:12.799 --> 17:15.602
You cannot let him
rule your life, Hakeem.

17:15.635 --> 17:19.939
You need people around you who
are gonna make you feel good.

17:19.972 --> 17:21.741
You know?

17:21.774 --> 17:23.376
Really good.

17:23.410 --> 17:24.777
(chuckles)

17:24.811 --> 17:27.046
Mm, babe.
Oh.

17:27.080 --> 17:28.215
Mmm.

17:28.248 --> 17:29.716
Babe, slow down.

17:29.749 --> 17:32.385
I need to tell
you something,

17:32.419 --> 17:35.622
and I want to make sure you're
in the right mood to hear it.

17:35.655 --> 17:37.724
Can we, like,
talk, no touching?
Hmm?

17:37.757 --> 17:39.226
(laughs)

17:39.259 --> 17:41.060
Really?

17:41.094 --> 17:42.262
No.

17:42.295 --> 17:44.097
Look, here's the thing.

17:47.967 --> 17:49.969
I think I'm in love.

17:53.473 --> 17:55.775
You're... you're in love?

17:55.808 --> 17:57.577
Yeah.

17:57.610 --> 17:59.412
(laughs)

17:59.446 --> 18:01.414
Look, I know it sound crazy.

18:01.448 --> 18:03.483
But I ain't never
feel this way in my life.

18:03.516 --> 18:06.919
But we still homies, right?
I still think you're dope.

18:06.953 --> 18:10.590
Yeah. Of course.

18:10.623 --> 18:12.325
Yes.
Great, great.

18:12.359 --> 18:14.694
So what did you have to tell me?

18:16.696 --> 18:19.098
Nothing. Nothing.

18:19.132 --> 18:22.169
I just wanted to
offer you my support

18:22.202 --> 18:24.437
with the Freda
thing, that's all.

18:24.471 --> 18:27.607
I don't know
wh-what's gonna happen.

18:27.640 --> 18:30.677
I got Cookie
and Laura helping me.

18:30.710 --> 18:33.313
Look, I'm sorry
about everything, Anika.

18:34.347 --> 18:36.316
Don't be.

18:51.531 --> 18:53.032
LUCIOUS:
Hey, what's up, Mal?

18:53.065 --> 18:55.668
So, listen. I've been
thinking about this song,

18:55.702 --> 19:00.006
and, uh... not really sure
which way I want to go with it.

19:00.039 --> 19:01.841
What you talking about?
You don't like my song?

19:01.874 --> 19:03.643
No, I love your song.
It's dope.

19:03.676 --> 19:08.147
But I got this other song
stuck in my head, and...

19:08.181 --> 19:09.882
I don't know,
maybe there's a way we could,

19:09.916 --> 19:11.651
you know, combine the two.

19:11.684 --> 19:13.152
Well, let me hear it.

19:13.186 --> 19:15.288
I mean, if it's good,
we'll use that one. Who cares?

19:15.322 --> 19:18.024
(gentle electronic music
playing)

19:18.057 --> 19:19.559
Nice.

19:23.596 --> 19:24.964
(laughs)

19:24.997 --> 19:26.165
It's cute.

19:26.199 --> 19:28.167
Cute. All right.

19:28.201 --> 19:29.569
Cute in a sexy kind
of cute.
Yeah.

19:35.708 --> 19:38.545
(instruments playing same song)

19:52.392 --> 19:54.160
(music stops)

19:54.193 --> 19:55.395
Yes, Jamal!

19:55.428 --> 19:58.064
Okay, I see why you wanted
to use the studio. (chuckles)

19:58.097 --> 20:00.099
I see you, boo.
You know, I've been thinking

20:00.132 --> 20:02.402
about what the song needs
to take it to the next level.

20:02.435 --> 20:04.203
Good. Me, too.
Yeah, you know
those keys

20:04.237 --> 20:06.873
are angelic, but they're
a little too happy, you feel me?

20:06.906 --> 20:08.408
Put a little edge on that.

20:08.441 --> 20:10.543
Put some stank on it. Run it
back. Let me hear it again.

20:10.577 --> 20:11.778
Mm-hmm, absolutely.
Y'all ready?
Yeah.

20:11.811 --> 20:13.713
JAMAL: All right.
COOKIE:
Go ahead, run it back.

20:13.746 --> 20:15.715
Come on,
what you waiting for?!

20:15.748 --> 20:17.617
Why y'all standing around
looking like you seen a ghost?

20:17.650 --> 20:19.619
What in the hell
is going on here?

20:19.652 --> 20:21.954
Are you serious, Jamal?
LUCIOUS:
You playing with me?

20:21.988 --> 20:23.390
That was her song?

20:23.423 --> 20:25.592
I'm not working with her, man.
COOKIE: Okay, so I left

20:25.625 --> 20:27.927
my spa mani-pedi to come
and deal with this?
Hear me out, please.

20:27.960 --> 20:29.896
LUCIOUS: Is this for real?
JAMAL: Just hear me out.

20:29.929 --> 20:31.063
COOKIE:
I don't even believe this.
Just wait, y'all!

20:31.097 --> 20:33.099
This is exactly why I needed
neutral ground.

20:33.132 --> 20:34.701
Now...

20:34.734 --> 20:37.304
I'm gonna need y'all to fuse
both of your songs together.

20:37.337 --> 20:38.371
I'm sorry, that's
not gonna happen.

20:38.405 --> 20:39.572
That's gonna happen.

20:39.606 --> 20:42.241
Charlie, bring up the mics,
please. Thank you.

20:42.275 --> 20:44.577
Here we go, flutes.
One, two, three, and...

20:44.611 --> 20:45.945
(instruments playing
gentle music)

20:51.451 --> 20:52.419
(music stops)

20:52.452 --> 20:53.486
Mom.
What?

20:53.520 --> 20:55.087
Your flutes are

20:55.121 --> 20:56.789
beautiful,
they're perfect.
I know that.

20:56.823 --> 20:58.991
They are. Your keyboard...

20:59.025 --> 21:01.027
(playing gentle music)

21:03.129 --> 21:04.431
...are beautiful.

21:04.464 --> 21:05.598
Uplifting, even.

21:05.632 --> 21:07.066
"Angelic" is what I said.

21:07.099 --> 21:08.134
Okay, angelic.

21:08.167 --> 21:09.902
But...

21:09.936 --> 21:12.472
Dad's beat and bass line
will bring it all together.

21:13.540 --> 21:15.475
(playing upbeat music)

21:21.648 --> 21:23.816
(music stops)

21:23.850 --> 21:24.817
That's the whole song.

21:24.851 --> 21:26.118
So this is what
I need from y'all.

21:26.152 --> 21:28.821
We are going to merge
these two songs together.

21:28.855 --> 21:30.790
Uh, that is not
gonna happen.
Mom,

21:30.823 --> 21:32.625
these musicians know literally
every single note of this song.

21:32.659 --> 21:33.993
And if y'all can just
work together

21:34.026 --> 21:35.962
for more than two seconds,
I promise you

21:35.995 --> 21:37.296
I can close this thing.
Look, y'all can

21:37.330 --> 21:38.831
play whatever game
y'all want to play,

21:38.865 --> 21:41.668
but at the end of the day,
this is an Empire song.

21:41.701 --> 21:43.035
Empire's paying
for this session.

21:43.069 --> 21:44.036
Actually, no.

21:44.070 --> 21:45.472
I am.

21:45.505 --> 21:47.306
(laughs)

21:47.340 --> 21:48.641
Dad.

21:48.675 --> 21:50.710
Your generation.

21:50.743 --> 21:52.679
Thank you.
All right, come on.

21:52.712 --> 21:54.013
Top.

21:54.046 --> 21:55.715
One, two, three, and...

21:55.748 --> 21:58.017
(upbeat music playing)

22:05.592 --> 22:06.826
(gentle music joins in)

22:06.859 --> 22:08.661
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!
No, no, no, no!

22:08.695 --> 22:10.062
Now what the hell
is that, man?!

22:10.096 --> 22:11.831
Oh, my...

22:11.864 --> 22:13.199
That don't work, Jamal. He...

22:13.232 --> 22:15.234
That-that flattened 13th
is killing the bass line.

22:15.267 --> 22:16.736
What?
You got to take that out.

22:16.769 --> 22:18.838
No, I'm not taking
that out, Lucious, no!

22:18.871 --> 22:22.208
Because, first of all, your damn
chorus is too long and scary.

22:22.241 --> 22:24.511
LUCIOUS: Now why don't you
just tell the truth?

22:24.544 --> 22:27.179
You're just trying to save
your dead label by using my son.

22:27.213 --> 22:28.848
That's the truth.
Oh, so now he's your son?

22:28.881 --> 22:31.050
Now he's your son, Lucious?
You hear this?

22:31.083 --> 22:32.719
That's it.

22:32.752 --> 22:34.921
I'm not working with her,
I told you.

22:34.954 --> 22:36.188
Choose.

22:36.222 --> 22:38.090
Yeah, you gonna have to choose.

22:38.124 --> 22:41.027
'Cause, I'm sorry,
this is not the Disney Channel.

22:41.060 --> 22:42.595
We have no happy ending.

22:42.629 --> 22:44.196
Never was a happy ending.

22:44.230 --> 22:45.865
This is an embarrassment
is what this is.

22:45.898 --> 22:47.700
Well, I don't know,

22:47.734 --> 22:49.569
I thought that
maybe y'all could choose

22:49.602 --> 22:51.704
to work together to possibly
do something that would not only

22:51.738 --> 22:53.239
change my life but y'all's, too.

22:54.607 --> 22:56.375
I guess I was wrong,
so I'm done.

22:56.409 --> 22:58.077
Jamal, baby...
No, Ma, I-I'm done.

23:00.279 --> 23:01.448
I'm gonna get him back.

23:01.481 --> 23:03.082
He needs me.
He lives to be me.

23:03.115 --> 23:04.884
He needs me.
And you're gonna
lose Hakeem as well.

23:04.917 --> 23:05.918
I got time
on my side.

23:05.952 --> 23:07.554
And I'm gonna rebuild him.

23:07.587 --> 23:09.922
Don't you bet on it.

23:09.956 --> 23:13.225
Hey... why don't we make a bet?

23:13.259 --> 23:14.561
Say word.

23:14.594 --> 23:16.563
When Hakeem wins...

23:16.596 --> 23:17.564
Hmm.

23:17.597 --> 23:19.231
...I get to release

23:19.265 --> 23:21.300
Jamal's next album
through Lyon Dynasty.

23:23.102 --> 23:26.405
And if your Freda Wack...

23:26.439 --> 23:29.275
happens to win,

23:29.308 --> 23:31.410
you can have Hakeem's.

23:31.444 --> 23:33.480
(chuckles)

23:33.513 --> 23:35.081
Bet.

23:35.114 --> 23:36.649
Bet.

23:36.683 --> 23:38.918
Put your shoes
in my face again.
Shut it.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.893
Okay, this is a battle rap.
Now, we just gonna throw you

23:46.926 --> 23:49.261
some subjects
and you flow, okay? Go.
(hip-hop beat playing)

23:49.295 --> 23:51.063
Phone.

23:51.097 --> 23:53.800
* Phone-- got it in my hand
right now *

23:53.833 --> 23:55.968
* Transferring money
to one of my bank accounts *

23:56.002 --> 23:58.237
* Same time, texting a shorty,
we going out *

23:58.270 --> 24:01.073
* Let her stand next to me
and give her a little shine *

24:01.107 --> 24:03.109
* He ain't even
from the streets, check *

24:03.142 --> 24:05.978
* And he want to be
the boss, check *

24:06.012 --> 24:08.014
* He a little fake mogul,
check *

24:08.047 --> 24:09.949
* And he jealous
of his brother, check *

24:09.982 --> 24:13.085
* I'm laughing at him 'cause
I ain't even worried 'bout him *

24:13.119 --> 24:15.622
* If it ain't Hollywood,
we ain't heard about it *

24:15.655 --> 24:18.758
* Young, rich and flashy,
can't nobody pass me *

24:18.791 --> 24:20.426
* Line 'em up,
I knock 'em down *

24:20.459 --> 24:22.428
* Shorty get at me
(whooping)

24:22.461 --> 24:25.998
* Rolly don't tick,
my whips bet they be nasty *

24:26.032 --> 24:29.001
* I got my own money,
I don't really need daddy *

24:29.035 --> 24:30.603
(crowd cheering)

24:30.637 --> 24:33.305
* Little boy with his nails
done, lookin' like a bitch *

24:33.339 --> 24:35.942
* He never had to struggle,
all he know is being rich *

24:35.975 --> 24:38.110
* Me versus dude is like
a kitten to a bull *

24:38.144 --> 24:40.680
* You know it's hunting season,
one for me and none for you *

24:40.713 --> 24:43.349
* Damn fool, boy, he know
little Freda win it all *

24:43.382 --> 24:45.484
* I'm a bitch, I'm a dog,
but a lion when I roar *

24:45.518 --> 24:48.120
* Check.

24:48.154 --> 24:51.958
JAMAL: I swear, man, the
way Mom and Dad argue,

24:51.991 --> 24:54.126
makes you want to
just say screw it.

24:54.160 --> 24:56.462
Know what I'm saying?
I could submit both songs.

24:56.495 --> 24:59.365
But, man, how you gonna win
with "screw it"?

24:59.398 --> 25:01.000
Don't ask, just take.

25:01.033 --> 25:04.003
You got Dad in you
and you got Mom in you, too.

25:04.036 --> 25:06.673
You got to take the parts
you need from both of them

25:06.706 --> 25:08.207
and fuse them together
for yourself.

25:08.240 --> 25:11.644
Ain't no Mom and Dad.

25:11.678 --> 25:14.413
They're business partners,
not your parents.

25:15.748 --> 25:17.149
It's all on you, Mal.

25:17.183 --> 25:19.051
Oh, CEO talk coming from you.

25:19.919 --> 25:21.020
(chuckles)

25:24.023 --> 25:26.392
So you gonna come see
me and Freda or what?

25:26.425 --> 25:29.495
Tell you this much though,
I want to see a show.

25:29.528 --> 25:30.663
I thought a battle was a show.

25:30.697 --> 25:32.531
Mm-mm. A battle
is a battle.

25:32.565 --> 25:34.233
And that's Freda's game;
you ain't got to try

25:34.266 --> 25:35.668
to follow
that little one-trick fool.

25:35.702 --> 25:37.604
You a MC, but you're
also a performer.

25:37.637 --> 25:38.905
